6 Program created by section 10.3 of this act to purchase and retire decreed or
7 certificated groundwater rights from willing sellers and to accept donations
8 of groundwater rights for retirement in order to:
9 (a) Protect the natural resources of this State;
10 (b) Address declining levels of groundwater; or
11 (c) Address conflicts with existing rights or with protectable interests
12 in existing domestic wells.
13 2. The Nevada Voluntary Water Rights Retirement Program must be
14 administered by the Director. [In administering the Program, the Director
15 shall, to the extent money is available in the Account for Retiring Water
16 Rights created by section 10.5 of this act, identify and purchase decreed or
17 certificated groundwater rights for retirement by the State Engineer
18 pursuant to section 8 of this act from persons willing to retire those
19 groundwater rights in groundwater basins where:
20 (a) An order issued by the State Engineer precludes the issuance of
21 permits for new appropriations of groundwater in the groundwater basin; or
22 (b) The retirement of groundwater rights in the groundwater basin
23 meets any purpose set forth in subsection 1.]
24 3. [The Director shall document in writing the purpose of each
25 decreed or certificated groundwater right that is purchased by or donated to
26 the Program and file the written document with the State Engineer.
27 4. When sufficient money is available in the Account for Retiring
28 Water Rights created by section 10.5 of this act, the Director may accept
29 applications for the purchase and retirement of decreed or certificated
30 groundwater rights.
31 5.] The Director shall not accept donations or applications for the
32 purchase and retirement of decreed or certificated groundwater rights after
33 June 30, 2035.
34 Sec. 17. 1. This section and sections 1 to 15, inclusive, of this act become
35 effective on July 1, 2025.
36 2. Section 10.5 of this act expires by limitation on June 30, 2035.
37 3. Section 16 of this act becomes effective on July 1, 2035.

